# Google Maps Platform API key for Photorealistic 3D Tiles (Map Tiles API).
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and paste your key there. Without a key,
# Freefall flies the greybox sandbox instead of Los Angeles (graceful fallback).
#
# Secure this CLIENT-SIDE key in Google Cloud (no server proxy needed):
#   1. Enable the "Map Tiles API" on a billing-enabled project.
#   2. Application restriction -> HTTP referrers: http://localhost:5173/*
#      (your actual Vite dev port) and your eventual https://<app>.vercel.app/*
#   3. API restriction -> restrict to the Map Tiles API only.
#   4. Set a daily quota cap on the Map Tiles API (runaway-loop guard).
#
# Vite only exposes VITE_-prefixed vars to import.meta.env. Restart `npm run dev`
# after editing env files.
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
